4:
My, oh my! Thanks again, Ernest! I
know how busy you are with your
job at the Academy...
7:
Think nothing of it. Your smile makes
it all worth it.
10:
That's right. How is your husband
doing? I was wondering if I could
play chess again with him
sometime...
14:
Hello, is there something I can help
you with?
18: Actually, we came to help you.
22:
You're Ernest, right? I'm Alk. We got a
request from Lera...
27:
Father sent another request, did he?
He never stops worrying...
30:
Thank you for coming, I really
appreciate it. I hope you didn't have
any trouble finding me.
35:
Wasn't any trouble at all. But, uh,
we're a little confused though. The
request only said you need help with
work, but didn't specify what kind.
37:
You're a researcher at Voluntas
Academy, right? If you're out in the
field, are you gathering materials or
escorting people in the
Kaleidoscope?
41:
Oh no, not quite. I've been doing
deliveries and repairs of equipment
today, and then I'll be off to help
train new adventurers...
44:
I've also got to collect medicinal
herbs for a clinic and help some
children with their studies at the
orphanage…
49: ...You're a jack of all trades, then?
53: Wow... So you're an adventurer, too?
57:
Helping people around the city gives
me a lot of opportunities. Being an
adventurer is quite convenient, in
fact.
62:
I see... I guess you're pretty famous
in Palpebra.
66:
Not as much as you two, I assure
you!
69:
You're well-known not only in the
Guild, but also at the Academy and
the orphanage, too.
71:
I'm a little jealous, to be honest. It
must be nice to be so loved in the
city.
75:
I don't know, Ernest. Everyone seems
to really like you.
85:
Ahaha, perhaps... I certainly hope
that's true.
87:
...Father and the others gave me a
place to belong.
91:
It sounds noble to suggest that I'm
simply returning their kindness, but I
think I just want to be appreciated.
110:
Aside from a little shock, it didn't look
like he had any serious injuries.
118:
Stella. Why did you jump in back
there?
120:
Alk, you followed up without any
hesitation either. Did you two have
some sort of plan?
125: I wanted to help that person.
138: Yeah... That's just the way Stella is.
140:
There wasn't any plan. I just jumped
in when I saw her go.
145:
...Is that so?
You two... are truly kind people.
156:
Alk, Stella. Would you like to be
friends?
159: I'd... love to keep working with you.
162:
Wonderful people like you are rare
to come by. I'd be interested in
getting to know you, if you'd allow it.
172:
Yeah. Besides, we know just the
place where we can continue our
chat.
185:
Are you sure it's okay that you
brought me here?
190:
We just showed a friend our home,
that's all.
194:
I suppose you're right. It's an honor
to be here with you.
197:
Thank you for bringing me to this
place. I look forward to our
adventurers together.
